title: View Photos of the New 2020 Porsche Taycan
text: The new Taycan is an electric sports sedan that marks a turning point for Porsche. Tesla has proven that there is a market for luxury EVs, and so Porsche is finally jumping into that fray with this new fastback sedan, which is slightly smaller than a Panamera and roughly the same length as a Tesla Model S. The Taycan will initially be offered in 750-horsepower Turbo S and 670-horsepower Turbo versions, both of which use a 93.0-kWh battery pack and an electric motor mounted in both the front and rear axles.
